WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.160
Today, we'll be talking about SageMaker

00:00:02.300 --> 00:00:04.800
and using RStudio Pro inside SageMaker

00:00:04.940 --> 00:00:06.840
for all of your R-based workflows.

00:00:07.860 --> 00:00:10.400
My name is Tom Mock. I'm the Posit Workbench Product Manager

00:00:10.540 --> 00:00:12.560
and helping with some of our integrations to companies

00:00:12.700 --> 00:00:15.260
like AWS and the SageMaker platform.

00:00:15.400 --> 00:00:17.200
And I'll be joined by my colleague, Gagan Deep,

00:00:17.340 --> 00:00:19.200
later on to go through a live demo.

00:00:20.100 --> 00:00:22.940
To start with, I'd like to cover some of the high level

00:00:23.059 --> 00:00:25.660
kind of value propositions of what RStudio Pro

00:00:25.799 --> 00:00:27.860
and SageMaker provides and some of the benefits

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.400
and kind of different trade-offs that are available for that.

00:00:31.260 --> 00:00:35.259
So let's jump into this. First off, we're really excited.

00:00:35.400 --> 00:00:36.700
This is a true kind of partnership

00:00:36.820 --> 00:00:39.860
that we have with the Amazon team and the SageMaker team.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:42.560
And we're really excited to kind of be able to offer

00:00:42.700 --> 00:00:44.599
our commercial offering of RStudio

00:00:45.220 --> 00:00:48.360
along with Amazon and SageMaker's platform.

00:00:48.500 --> 00:00:51.720
So enabling our customers to do this really powerful machine

00:00:51.860 --> 00:00:53.820
learning and enhance their workloads

00:00:53.959 --> 00:00:57.060
beyond what's available on their local laptops.

00:00:58.860 --> 00:01:02.259
Ultimately, we can break down kind of the benefits of SageMaker

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:04.400
with RStudio Pro into four topics.

00:01:04.519 --> 00:01:06.519
And we'll kind of dive into these a bit deeper.

00:01:07.160 --> 00:01:10.760
So number one, RStudio Pro on SageMaker is a managed service.

00:01:10.900 --> 00:01:14.519
So this massively simplifies the administration.

00:01:14.660 --> 00:01:17.320
And you don't have to have a robust IT team

00:01:17.459 --> 00:01:19.120
to manage over everything.

00:01:19.260 --> 00:01:22.519
It's managed through the SageMaker platform as a hosted service.

00:01:23.660 --> 00:01:26.160
Additionally, especially compared to a local laptop,

00:01:26.160 --> 00:01:29.900
SageMaker with RStudio Pro provides this flexible compute.

00:01:30.019 --> 00:01:33.019
And you don't have to figure out how to spin up new servers.

00:01:33.160 --> 00:01:35.419
You can actually just use a dropdown within RStudio

00:01:35.559 --> 00:01:37.419
to select different sizing of your environment

00:01:37.559 --> 00:01:39.760
for both RAM and CPU, et cetera.

00:01:41.160 --> 00:01:42.760
Additionally, the SageMaker platform

00:01:42.900 --> 00:01:45.820
comes with strict security and compliance benefits.

00:01:45.959 --> 00:01:48.500
So things like SOC2, FedRAMP, HIPAA,

00:01:48.620 --> 00:01:52.620
and additional other kind of security confirmations and compliance.

00:01:52.760 --> 00:01:55.220
It's really useful and needed for our customers

00:01:55.720 --> 00:01:58.120
in banking or pharma or health care, for example.

00:01:59.120 --> 00:02:01.480
And then lastly, SageMaker also allows customers

00:02:01.620 --> 00:02:03.680
to use their existing cloud budgets.

00:02:03.820 --> 00:02:06.279
So for a lot of customers, they actually have budgets

00:02:06.419 --> 00:02:10.279
that are set aside for purchasing compute through cloud like AWS.

00:02:10.419 --> 00:02:12.679
And you can use some of that budget to purchase licenses

00:02:12.820 --> 00:02:16.360
for RStudio Pro that is then used inside SageMaker.

00:02:16.479 --> 00:02:20.360
Again, alleviating some of the struggles with purchasing

00:02:20.479 --> 00:02:22.479
or figuring out how to get this budget approved.

00:02:23.339 --> 00:02:26.020
Overall, you can kind of have this nice little table here

00:02:26.139 --> 00:02:28.979
that compares pure SageMaker to RStudio Pro

00:02:29.119 --> 00:02:31.279
in addition to the core SageMaker platform.

00:02:32.419 --> 00:02:34.979
Both SageMaker and RStudio Pro on SageMaker

00:02:35.119 --> 00:02:36.880
are flexible computing environments.

00:02:37.020 --> 00:02:40.479
So actually backed by these ephemeral EC2 instances

00:02:40.619 --> 00:02:42.820
and Docker images that are loaded into it.

00:02:43.440 --> 00:02:46.740
Both have a dedicated home directory for persistent files

00:02:46.880 --> 00:02:48.220
or other things like that.

00:02:48.339 --> 00:02:51.020
And then the SageMaker platform is a little bit different.

00:02:51.020 --> 00:02:54.919
It's dedicated for persistent files, R and Python package installs,

00:02:55.059 --> 00:02:56.820
configuration settings, different things

00:02:56.960 --> 00:03:00.020
that you want your user kind of experience to be the same.

00:03:00.880 --> 00:03:03.520
The main difference at this point is that SageMaker

00:03:03.660 --> 00:03:06.759
is really like a hosted version of Jupyter or JupyterLab.

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:11.559
And then RStudio adds the additional RStudio IDE experience

00:03:11.679 --> 00:03:13.419
on top of SageMaker's compute.

00:03:14.520 --> 00:03:17.479
For SageMaker with JupyterLab, you're primarily using Python.

00:03:17.580 --> 00:03:19.619
So you can use packages like Boto3

00:03:19.740 --> 00:03:22.820
to interact with AWS and different services.

00:03:22.940 --> 00:03:25.419
And then in R, there's the pause R package

00:03:25.539 --> 00:03:27.279
that allows you to do very similar things

00:03:27.419 --> 00:03:30.520
and interact with all sorts of AWS services,

00:03:30.639 --> 00:03:32.240
in addition to SageMaker.

00:03:33.240 --> 00:03:36.820
And then lastly, both SageMaker and RStudio Pro inside SageMaker

00:03:36.940 --> 00:03:39.720
allow you to leverage specific SageMaker machine

00:03:39.839 --> 00:03:41.419
learning capabilities.

00:03:41.539 --> 00:03:44.479
Both are really using the SageMaker Python SDK

00:03:44.619 --> 00:03:46.220
or software developer kit.

00:03:46.919 --> 00:03:50.080
In SageMaker, you primarily call it natively through Python.

00:03:50.220 --> 00:03:53.460
And then in RStudio, you actually wrap some of the commands in R

00:03:53.580 --> 00:03:56.720
using the same SageMaker Python SDK,

00:03:56.860 --> 00:03:59.259
but wrapping it with the reticulate R package,

00:03:59.380 --> 00:04:01.919
allowing you to call Python directly from R.

00:04:02.820 --> 00:04:05.320
So really, the environment is the same for both of them,

00:04:05.460 --> 00:04:07.779
but providing kind of a different user interface

00:04:07.919 --> 00:04:11.320
with the same packages and persistent files behind the scenes.

00:04:11.759 --> 00:04:14.580
As far as a lot of the customers that we've seen

00:04:14.720 --> 00:04:17.760
kind of be ideal fits for RStudio Pro and SageMaker,

00:04:18.380 --> 00:04:20.859
number one, users who are already invested

00:04:20.980 --> 00:04:24.579
or are investing in the AWS ecosystem.

00:04:24.720 --> 00:04:26.380
So maybe they're already using SageMaker,

00:04:26.519 --> 00:04:29.779
but want to leverage R there and really like using RStudio.

00:04:30.420 --> 00:04:33.260
Or maybe they're using RStudio on a desktop

00:04:33.380 --> 00:04:36.079
and want to make use of the robust machine learning tooling

00:04:36.220 --> 00:04:38.660
and skilled compute available inside SageMaker.

00:04:38.920 --> 00:04:41.920
Additionally, because SageMaker is a hosted environment

00:04:42.059 --> 00:04:45.320
and the AWS team is actually managing the infrastructure for you,

00:04:46.260 --> 00:04:48.519
users who lack IT support

00:04:48.660 --> 00:04:51.059
or don't necessarily want to commit the resources

00:04:51.200 --> 00:04:53.920
needed to maintain a fully custom environment

00:04:54.059 --> 00:04:56.519
can go through this with kind of a ready to go,

00:04:56.660 --> 00:04:58.760
spin it up kind of very quickly environment.

00:04:59.720 --> 00:05:03.600
And then lastly, really emphasizing that for RStudio desktop users,

00:05:03.720 --> 00:05:06.799
at a certain point, your laptop or your computer

00:05:06.899 --> 00:05:08.660
at a certain point, your laptop

00:05:08.799 --> 00:05:11.700
or even your workstation is going to run out of compute.

00:05:11.839 --> 00:05:14.739
Maybe you need 64 gigs or 128 gigs of RAM.

00:05:15.799 --> 00:05:18.200
With SageMaker, you can scale up kind of as large

00:05:18.339 --> 00:05:19.839
as it'll allow you to go.

00:05:19.959 --> 00:05:21.899
And then whenever you're done, you can actually shut down

00:05:22.040 --> 00:05:24.399
that environment and stop accruing cost.

00:05:24.540 --> 00:05:28.140
So you can have these kind of cost efficient scaling out as needed.

00:05:30.899 --> 00:05:35.100
As far as some of the additional benefits of RStudio Pro on SageMaker,

00:05:35.200 --> 00:05:37.899
since again, RStudio is a managed service,

00:05:38.040 --> 00:05:40.940
customers don't have to really worry about managing installations

00:05:41.059 --> 00:05:44.559
of R and Python or even installing a Posit Workbench

00:05:44.700 --> 00:05:47.059
slash RStudio Pro itself in the environment.

00:05:47.200 --> 00:05:48.799
It's already kind of ready to go.

00:05:49.500 --> 00:05:52.040
Additionally, our software product called Launcher

00:05:52.160 --> 00:05:55.459
is working behind the scenes with SageMaker internally

00:05:55.600 --> 00:05:58.940
that allows you to create these individually sized

00:05:59.059 --> 00:06:00.660
and isolated sessions.

00:06:00.799 --> 00:06:03.100
So you can have a gigantic session, run a model,

00:06:03.260 --> 00:06:06.239
leave it running and then go to a much smaller session

00:06:06.359 --> 00:06:07.940
with say like eight gigs of RAM

00:06:08.059 --> 00:06:11.399
and then do some computation there or exploratory data analysis

00:06:11.540 --> 00:06:14.000
while your large model training is occurring.

00:06:15.260 --> 00:06:17.660
Additionally, RStudio Pro on SageMaker

00:06:17.799 --> 00:06:22.260
has direct integration with identity access management through AWS.

00:06:22.399 --> 00:06:24.700
So you can use a lot of the other AWS services

00:06:24.839 --> 00:06:26.600
without needing to reauthenticate

00:06:26.739 --> 00:06:28.399
or move around a whole bunch of credentials,

00:06:28.540 --> 00:06:31.059
kind of log in once and use a lot of other different things.

00:06:32.059 --> 00:06:35.059
You can also use, again, these pre-allocated cloud budgets.

00:06:35.200 --> 00:06:38.760
So it's pretty often that we see some of these customers

00:06:38.899 --> 00:06:42.600
have a lot of money tied up into their cloud budgets,

00:06:42.720 --> 00:06:44.100
and they can use a small portion of that

00:06:44.220 --> 00:06:47.859
to purchase these RStudio Pro licenses to be used within SageMaker.

00:06:48.959 --> 00:06:52.760
And then lastly, reiterating that for some of our compliant

00:06:52.899 --> 00:06:55.059
and secure needs of customers,

00:06:55.200 --> 00:06:58.899
that SageMaker already has SOC2, FedRAMP, HIPAA compliance

00:06:59.500 --> 00:07:03.339
and is adding additional compliance kind of certifications over time.

00:07:06.239 --> 00:07:08.700
I do want to call out some of the trade-offs or differences,

00:07:08.839 --> 00:07:11.640
though, between a self-managed Posit Workbench

00:07:11.760 --> 00:07:14.959
that includes RStudio Pro as well as JupyterLab and VS Code

00:07:15.100 --> 00:07:17.260
versus RStudio Pro on SageMaker.

00:07:18.100 --> 00:07:20.700
Number one, self-managed Posit Workbench

00:07:20.839 --> 00:07:23.299
provides complete flexibility about how you set up

00:07:23.440 --> 00:07:25.399
and configure and administer Workbench.

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:27.260
You do need an IT admin,

00:07:27.459 --> 00:07:30.100
but you can really set up a really custom environment

00:07:30.220 --> 00:07:32.420
and have access to all these different things you need.

00:07:33.459 --> 00:07:35.600
This does come at the cost of responsibility.

00:07:35.720 --> 00:07:38.600
You do have to have that IT admin persona

00:07:38.720 --> 00:07:42.100
to come in and maintain, update the environment and the infrastructure.

00:07:42.619 --> 00:07:45.459
But if you really want that customization, that's a good route.

00:07:45.600 --> 00:07:49.220
And you can run it through an Amazon EC2 instance

00:07:49.359 --> 00:07:53.619
or even use clusters such as ECS for Kubernetes

00:07:53.760 --> 00:07:56.700
or parallel cluster for Slurm on AWS.

00:07:58.019 --> 00:08:01.059
Importantly, RStudio on SageMaker is this managed service.

00:08:01.200 --> 00:08:03.000
So the responsibility for the software

00:08:03.119 --> 00:08:05.119
and the environment resides with AWS.

00:08:05.260 --> 00:08:07.600
You actually work through the AWS support team,

00:08:07.720 --> 00:08:09.619
as well as in some cases, the Posit support team,

00:08:09.760 --> 00:08:12.519
if you run into trouble, instead of the individual customer

00:08:12.660 --> 00:08:14.519
kind of only working through their IT admin.

00:08:16.019 --> 00:08:20.160
And lastly, while Posit Workbench has access to multiple editors,

00:08:20.299 --> 00:08:24.660
it has RStudio, it has VS Code, as well as Jupyter and JupyterLab.

00:08:25.399 --> 00:08:28.320
The SageMaker environment has the RStudio IDE,

00:08:28.459 --> 00:08:30.859
as far as the RStudio Pro integration.

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:34.559
And then Amazon SageMaker Studio also provides a managed

00:08:34.700 --> 00:08:37.359
kind of Jupyter, JupyterLab experience.

00:08:37.500 --> 00:08:40.159
It does not have the same VS Code integration

00:08:40.900 --> 00:08:42.500
that Posit Workbench does.

00:08:43.059 --> 00:08:44.159
So there are some different trade-offs

00:08:44.299 --> 00:08:46.799
and just kind of design decisions as far as what you want.

00:08:46.919 --> 00:08:48.599
If you want this really custom environment

00:08:48.719 --> 00:08:50.760
to kind of set it up exactly as you want,

00:08:50.900 --> 00:08:52.320
or you have different needs,

00:08:52.479 --> 00:08:56.080
you can self-manage or install your own software

00:08:56.219 --> 00:08:58.219
into traditional infrastructure,

00:08:58.359 --> 00:09:01.479
or you can go this fully managed route through Amazon SageMaker.

00:09:03.059 --> 00:09:05.419
Before I turn it over to my colleague,

00:09:05.559 --> 00:09:08.520
I'm also going to share some of the resources.

00:09:08.659 --> 00:09:12.419
So if you do have questions about getting started with SageMaker,

00:09:12.559 --> 00:09:15.320
you can go to Posit.co slash SageMaker.

00:09:15.880 --> 00:09:19.880
This has all the information about getting started with RStudio Pro

00:09:20.020 --> 00:09:22.520
on SageMaker, maybe doing a free trial

00:09:22.640 --> 00:09:24.919
where you can evaluate its use for your team.

00:09:25.940 --> 00:09:28.679
Or you can even talk to a salesperson here

00:09:28.820 --> 00:09:30.979
or a colleague at Posit

00:09:31.119 --> 00:09:33.679
to talk about doing some of the integration work as needed.

00:09:34.619 --> 00:09:36.719
With that, I'm going to pause, stop screen sharing

00:09:36.840 --> 00:09:38.979
